INSTALLATION
============

Dependencies:
-------------

| Ubuntu                 | Fedora                | Version   |
|------------------------|-----------------------|-----------|
| cmake                  | cmake                 | >= 2.8    |
| debhelper              | debhelper             | >= 7      |
| pkg-config             | pkgconf-pkg-config    | >= 0.26   |
| build-essential        | "Development Tools"   | N/A       |
| python3                | python3               | >= 3.6.7  |
| python3-gi             | pygobject3            | >= 3.14   |
| gir1.2-gtk-3.0         | python3-gobject       | >= 3.14   |
| libgtk-3-dev           | gtk3-devel            | >= 3.14   |
| libglib2.0-dev         | glib2-devel           | >= 2.40.2 |
| gobject-introspection  | gobject-introspection | >= 1.40.0 |



Manual Installation:
--------------------

$ git clone https://github.com/gcleaner/gcleaner-python.git
$ cd gcleaner-python
$ mkdir build
$ cd build
$ cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr ..
$ make
$ sudo make install
$ gcleaner

Note: If you are a developer, check the CMakeLists.txt file and
copy manually the files to the corrects paths.



Manual Uninstall:
-----------------

There isn't one way yet



PPA:
----

There isn one, but it does not working well yet




General Notes:
--------------

If the gcleaner icon doesn't appear, run:
$ sudo gtk-update-icon-cache /usr/share/icons/hicolor/

Report bugs at https://github.com/gcleaner/gcleaner-python/issues
